{meta: title A Faded Rose A Broken Heart}
{meta: artist Hank Snow}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]I'm waiting by the garden wall
[G7]Where roses bloom neath summer [C]skies
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
You pressed one rose bud to you lips
[G7]The night we said our last [C]good-bye
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
[F]The rose you kissed is faded now [C]dear
[G7]And love is gone since we're apart
[C]You went your way and left me behind
[G7]A faded rose a broken [C]heart
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
I never knew that love so sweet
[G7]Could prove so bitter in the [C]end
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
I've tried to smile but all in vain
[G7]For love is dead I can't [C]pretend
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 6}
[F]Someday your heart will break and then [C]dear
[G7]You'll want me back and tears will start
[C]When you recall the one you left
[G7]A faded rose a broken [C]heart
{end_of_verse}
